header.gameNote: ATLANTIC SUN TR AT JOHNSON CITY TN

article.headline: ETSU 77, Lipscomb 72
article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. (AP) -- Courtney Pigram scored 21 points as East Tennessee State defeated Lipscomb 77-72 Friday night in the semifinals of the Atlantic Sun Conference tournament. Top-seeded ETSU (24-8) will play second-seeded Belmont in Saturday's 4 p.m. championship game. The winner earns the league's automatic bid to the NCAA tournament. Pigram, the league's player of the year, overcame an 0-for-5 start from the field and didn't score in the first 16 minutes. Freshman Mike Smith added 17 points for ETSU. Brad Nuckles added 12 and Eryk Thomas had 11. Lipscomb (18-13) was led by Brian Fisk's 20 points. Trey Williams added 19, all in the second half, for the Bisons, while Eddie Ard had 16 and Jason Hopkins had 11. Lipscomb led by as many as seven points in a highly competitive first half before ETSU then went on a 17-10 run to close the half. Pigram's 3-point basket just before the buzzer made it 35-35, the eighth tie of the first half. Pigram continued early in the second half, making a 3-point play to put ETSU up 38-35. When Nuckles scored inside to make it 40-35, ETSU never gave up the lead. Lipscomb pulled within one on a tip-in by Fisk, who was fouled while scoring with a minute left, but he missed a free throw that would have tied the game.
